snippet: The blaze has easily overcome barriers meant to contain it, turning computer models of how it will burn into futile predictors, officials said.
abstract: Officials say Rocky Fire, which has spread to 70,000 acres in California, remains only 20 percent contained after six days of hard-fought effort by firefighters; has defied expectations of normal wildfire behavior, crossing streets and fire lines and consuming acreage at alarming pace.
lead_paragraph: The blaze has easily overcome barriers meant to contain it, turning computer models of how it will burn into futile predictors, officials said.

headline.main: California Fire, Aided by Drought, Defies Tactics to Defeat It
headline.print_headline: California Fire, Aided by Drought, Defies Tactics to Defeat It
